Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We’ve fought under gravity \Nseveral times now, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.34,0:00:19.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“You judge a man by his looks”!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.71,0:00:21.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Randy, you’re the one \Nwho always says that!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.91,0:00:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to interrupt your meal!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.66,0:00:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You’ve been ordered to sortie!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.21,0:00:31.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Wulgaru army has broken \Npast our absolute defense zone!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.74,0:02:06.55,Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,“Defensive Battle at\NCosmopolitan Academy (First Part)”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.94,0:02:15.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Delish! Ashagi, ish dis \Nyour weal calling in life?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.37,0:02:17.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you eating?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.79,0:02:19.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The operation has already started!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.83,0:02:22.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m bored stiff after \Nall of this waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.96,0:02:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Izuru! How was \Nyour date with Teoria?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.89,0:02:34.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“How,” huh? Everyone saw \Nhow it went down, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.47,0:02:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We only got to talk for a \Nbit before I was summoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.69,0:02:40.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But-but a date is still a date!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.60,0:02:44.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You suddenly grew closer or something \Nalong those lines, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.23,0:02:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I’ll admit I do \Nthink we’ve grown closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.78,0:02:50.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ange is running late!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.16,0:02:51.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What could be keeping her?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.99,0:02:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black 6 is already in position \Nto sortie and will be
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.54,0:02:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,working independently of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.76,0:03:03.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We just received an emergency \Ncall from Captain Amane.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.45,0:03:06.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our vessel will change its current \Ncourse and return to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.92,0:03:10.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, Black 6 will continue \Nto head toward the frontlines.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.09,0:03:14.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We’ve identified an enemy \Ndetachment headed for Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.60,0:03:18.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We believe they are targeting \NGurantseere Cosmopolitan Academy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.19,0:03:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our school...?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.62,0:03:42.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The allied armies of Bela-Russia,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.46,0:03:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Great Chinese Alliance and the MJP
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.36,0:03:47.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are currently fighting \Nthe Wulgaru fleet that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.51,0:03:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has broken past the \Nabsolute defense zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.97,0:03:51.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, we noticed a detachment
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.83,0:03:54.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that is acting independently \Nof the main fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.39,0:03:57.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here is an image of the enemy \Nsquad headed toward Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.68,0:03:59.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s a small group...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.24,0:04:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn’t the fighter in front
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.76,0:04:04.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,look like the one Ange \Njust recently thrashed?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.90,0:04:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are they going after the academy?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.48,0:04:09.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to Commander Simon,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.07,0:04:13.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they probably intend to steal \Nsome DNA samples from the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.11,0:04:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are signs that the enemy stole a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.20,0:04:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,vast amount of Earth’s \Ndata the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.20,0:04:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This attack is probably related \Nto the information they obtained.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.86,0:04:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the moment, our vessel \Nis the closest one to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.75,0:04:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth will also launch \Ntheir reserve fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.00,0:04:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are to go and offer our support.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.43,0:04:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Klein, what are you doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.69,0:04:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have not received orders to sortie.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.60,0:04:46.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m not going to let \Nyou hog all of the glory.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.33,0:04:48.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m going to take \Nthese lamata for myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.48,0:04:50.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Restrain yourself, Klein!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.40,0:04:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The purpose of this operation
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.42,0:04:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is to verify the information \NLumes has obtained.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.57,0:04:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a reconnaissance mission \Nto determine whether or not
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.41,0:05:01.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Earthlings possess prime DNA \Nsamples on their home world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.66,0:05:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, your wounds \Nhave not yet healed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.58,0:05:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These injuries can’t hold me back!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.00,0:05:11.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the genes are there, I’ll \Nsimply swipe them all!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.97,0:05:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m gonna restore \Nthe honor I’ve lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.55,0:05:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Klein!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.84,0:05:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These are my lamata!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.98,0:05:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lumes, remain where you \Nare for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.40,0:05:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. We shall charge \Nthrough, just as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.40,0:05:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With two squads, this will make a \Ncoordinated effort all the easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.82,0:05:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Going by the looks of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.45,0:05:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Klein may very well fire \Nat friend and foe alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.55,0:05:40.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remain on standby for now \Nand see how things progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.74,0:05:44.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My fleet shall work to maintain \Nour current standing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.83,0:05:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well, Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.74,0:05:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My plans have gone horribly awry...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.28,0:05:56.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No... Perhaps he predicted that \Nthere was a chance this may happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.39,0:06:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here is the information on Earth \Nthat I obtained the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.81,0:06:05.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to this, the Earthlings \Nhave a facility where they
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.85,0:06:07.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,combine advanced genes on their
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.89,0:06:11.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,home planet to produce highly \Nadvanced individuals.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.88,0:06:13.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What an absurd species.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.65,0:06:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ultimately, they have created nothing \Nbut a poor imitation of our civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.37,0:06:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet even so, fascinating individuals \Ncan appear on occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.41,0:06:27.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If not for that, this \Nwould be far too tiresome.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.62,0:06:33.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here is the information on \NPleguzesia Teoria and Daneel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.54,0:06:35.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As suspected, they are on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.23,0:06:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My prediction was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.28,0:06:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps my younger sister’s \Ngenes were calling out to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.60,0:06:45.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem that Pleguzesia \Nis near this facility.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.89,0:06:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do not know if those \Nof Earth apprehended her
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.14,0:06:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or if she went to Earth \Non her own accord.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.65,0:06:54.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you reported to my brother yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.65,0:06:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have not told anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.53,0:06:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I felt that it would be appropriate \Nto report to you first.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.49,0:07:00.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.78,0:07:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Henceforth, you are to be \Nmy eyes and ears as you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.82,0:07:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,continue to gather information.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.46,0:07:07.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it safe to assume that you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.17,0:07:08.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,do not want me to submit \Nan official report?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.16,0:07:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do not want to distress \Nmy older brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.38,0:07:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And if this information came to light,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.52,0:07:18.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ambitious fools would try their \Nupmost best to topple our clan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.31,0:07:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is my younger \Nsister doing on Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.92,0:07:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until that is made clear, \Ndo not tell anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.57,0:07:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.06,0:07:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will speak with my brother
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.78,0:07:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and see to it that you \Nare sent to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.69,0:07:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I must take other \Nmeasures, just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.65,0:07:41.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think that he had foreseen \Nthat I may not land on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.70,0:07:43.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pleguzes Jiart...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.36,0:07:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just how far can his eyes \Nsee into the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.67,0:08:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I imagine the Wulgaru fleet we’re \Ncurrently facing on the frontlines
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.13,0:08:04.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is a diversion meant \Nto draw our attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.30,0:08:06.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think their real target is Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.93,0:08:10.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn’t this the first time they’ve \Nlanded a direct attack on Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.85,0:08:12.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope everyone evacuates in time...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.94,0:08:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We just received some new \Ninformation from Commander Simon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.72,0:08:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The commander of the enemy’s \Ninfiltration squad is Klein.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.90,0:08:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Supposedly he is one of the \NWulgaru’s Military Commanders.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.32,0:08:22.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Military Commander?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.57,0:08:24.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What’s that? Sounds kinda tough!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.95,0:08:27.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once you’ve entered combat air \Nspace, launch out of your cockpits.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.91,0:08:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, our main ship will \Nengage in artillery combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.75,0:08:32.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, prepare to sortie.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.17,0:08:35.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here are the routes we expect \Nthe enemy to take to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.50,0:08:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s hard to say whether we \Ncan catch up with them or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.30,0:08:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, they may breach \Nthe earth’s atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.54,0:08:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The GDF’s reserve fleet has \Nreached the first line of defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.92,0:08:47.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They will engage in combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.98,0:09:01.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think those measly \Nships are enough to stop me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.44,0:09:04.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speed up! We’re gonna \Nsend these wimps reeling!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.71,0:09:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Topeka of the GDF squadron Providence \Nhas been severely damaged!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.88,0:09:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Galveston and Little Rock \Nhave been destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.71,0:09:23.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy fleet hasn’t \Nsuffered any losses!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.42,0:09:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They will enter range within 20 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.80,0:09:27.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All ships, prepare to launch an assault.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.78,0:09:29.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are free to use \Nall of your artillery.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.68,0:09:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Commence fire once enemy \Nfighters are within range.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.32,0:09:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your targets are the enemy \Nsquad on track for Earth!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.60,0:09:38.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy fighters seem to have \Nrather advance evasion systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.11,0:09:39.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m not sure if we’ll hit them...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.52,0:09:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don’t have to hit them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.65,0:09:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We just have to slow them down a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.28,0:09:48.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never expected our main ship \Nto engage in actual combat...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.03,0:09:50.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That goes to show how \Ndire the situation is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.70,0:09:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Depending on how things \Ngo, we may find ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.86,0:09:54.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,strapped to a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.35,0:09:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That isn’t funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.00,0:09:59.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I always get a Rank \NC at target practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.00,0:10:09.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All ships, blast off!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.99,0:10:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reinforcements?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.41,0:10:41.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don’t have time \Nto play with them!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.00,0:10:49.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You’re in the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.06,0:11:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy squad has \Nsuffered minor damages!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.20,0:11:16.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The enemies are moving at high speeds,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.79,0:11:18.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,allowing them to dodge our attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.62,0:11:20.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even when we do hit them, \Nit doesn’t do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.67,0:11:22.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As suspected, it looks like \Nthey are equipped with
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.83,0:11:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,high-performance defense systems.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.62,0:11:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah... They’ll get away if we \Nuse normal shells and artillery.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.43,0:11:31.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that might work...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.92,0:11:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have an idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.80,0:11:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I modified the weapon we used at Ceres.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.98,0:11:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s a powerful \Nlong-range optical weapon
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.18,0:11:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that pierces through objects \Nat the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.23,0:11:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I’m afraid the enemy will \Nnotice before we can fire a shot
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.27,0:11:45.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if we don’t snipe from \Na substantial distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.24,0:11:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap! At this rate, they’re \Ngonna break through.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.53,0:11:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But their speed has definitely dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.51,0:12:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they maintain this pace, \Nwe should make it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.96,0:12:02.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to stop the Wulgaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.54,0:12:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can’t let them lay a single \Nfinger on our old school.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.41,0:12:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your assignment is to evaluate \Nyourself and then surpass yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.00,0:12:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You’ve reached the \Ndesignated airspace!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.96,0:12:17.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Team Rabbits, prepare to sortie.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.43,0:12:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we are going to change \NGold 4’s armament.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.38,0:12:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We’re changing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.39,0:12:28.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Team Rabbits, blast off!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.57,0:13:55.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go to Hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.45,0:14:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You still haven’t seen nothin’ yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.99,0:14:05.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I dare you to come at me all \Nat once, you pathetic wimps!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.15,0:14:08.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even in mass, you’re nothing \Nbefore the great Black 6!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.23,0:14:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s one feisty pilot, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.05,0:14:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Supposedly this is Ange \NKuroki’s fighting style.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.92,0:14:17.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Compared to him, Patrick is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.47,0:14:20.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamaki isn’t coming, is she...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.22,0:14:24.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get yer act together, Patrick!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.10,0:14:25.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to all that vigor \Nyou had just a minute ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.10,0:14:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like I’m the type that \Nuses love as energy in my fights...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.06,0:14:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go meet your maker!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.78,0:14:35.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Tamaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.24,0:14:36.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dang, they’re the polar opposites.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.89,0:14:38.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Black 6, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.49,0:14:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope this is the only time we have to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.34,0:14:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,fight alongside someone like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.92,0:14:53.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They dived into inner space!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.00,0:14:54.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s go after them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.91,0:14:58.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! We’re outfitted for \Nfighting in outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.22,0:14:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we get caught in Earth’s gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.89,0:15:01.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we’ll become shooting stars \Nand get burned to a crisp!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.64,0:15:03.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red 5 and Blue 1,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.43,0:15:05.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,use Rose 3 as a shield \Nand descend to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.92,0:15:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will that actually work?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.88,0:15:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rose 3 is capable of entering the \Nearth’s atmosphere in its basic form.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.48,0:15:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you cling to the back of \NRose 3 while its shield is up,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.23,0:15:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue 1 and Red 5 should be \Nable to handle the entry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.72,0:15:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Purple 2, stay there on standby.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.92,0:15:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Help direct the units and \Ncoordinate their formations.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.45,0:15:25.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger. I will begin calculating their \Nspeed of descent and angle of incidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.62,0:15:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We’re off and away!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.63,0:15:33.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m sending you my \Norbital calculations.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.74,0:15:38.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rose 3 is faster than their fighters,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.13,0:15:39.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so you’ll just barely beat them there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.09,0:15:42.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you stray from this \Ncourse even a little,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.43,0:15:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you’ll wind up at a totally \Ndifferent location. Be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.04,0:15:48.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it! I’m heading on out!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.86,0:15:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We’re falling!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.32,0:16:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My unit’s surface temperature \Nis rapidly increasing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.82,0:16:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We’re still in the green!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.11,0:16:03.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamaki, up the speed!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.19,0:16:06.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rose 3, you can do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.48,0:16:32.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We made it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.86,0:16:42.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.07,0:16:44.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did your unit get damaged?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.45,0:16:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s just heavier \Nthan I was expecting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.37,0:16:47.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Relax!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.42,0:16:52.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as you keep your \Ncool, you can handle this!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.50,0:16:55.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it! Keep my cool... Keep my cool...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.67,0:17:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can’t believe we’re running \Naway when the enemy is right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.64,0:17:10.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can’t be helped...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.18,0:17:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What’s going on up there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.52,0:17:13.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s the Fail Five!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.80,0:17:15.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Fail Five?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.73,0:17:19.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Blue 1, Rose 3 and Red \N5 are up there fighting!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.73,0:17:21.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean Izuru, Asagi and Tamaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.61,0:17:23.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hang in there! Fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.25,0:17:34.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One fighter down!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.54,0:17:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can see our school from here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.64,0:17:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s going to take a while \Nbefore Gold 4 is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.27,0:17:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please buy some time!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.17,0:17:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are a bunch of enemy fighters!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.72,0:17:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us what to do, Kei.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.55,0:17:48.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Klein is their primary fighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.54,0:17:52.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone mark him while the other two \Ndeal with the remaining fighters.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.85,0:17:57.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru, you should defeat Klein.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.75,0:17:59.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tamaki and I will handle the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.02,0:18:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.48,0:18:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red 5 is superior in combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.03,0:18:06.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the others to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.85,0:18:08.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You do your job as the ace!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.45,0:18:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. I’m leaving \Nthe rest to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.99,0:18:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru was Team Rabbit’s ace pilot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.25,0:18:19.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to admit it, but he’s a \Nbetter pilot than either of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.59,0:18:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we should focus on doing what we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.66,0:18:26.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dang! And here I thought \NI was our ace pilot!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.80,0:18:29.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.14,0:18:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All three of them have high Harmonic \NLevels, especially Blue 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.85,0:18:35.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This may be his highest level yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.76,0:18:40.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The primitive creature \NI fought last time?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.09,0:18:41.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excellent!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.05,0:18:42.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s have a return match!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.03,0:18:44.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My weapons don’t work on him...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.92,0:18:45.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.07,0:18:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for waitin’!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.73,0:18:53.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold 4 is now on the scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.49,0:18:55.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Izuru and the others have already \Nmade contact with the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.83,0:18:57.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please prepare to fire immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.83,0:18:59.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t be in such a rush!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.46,0:19:02.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Optical weapons take a delicate touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.04,0:19:03.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They pierce through the \Nenemy at the speed of light,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.96,0:19:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so as long as your aim is good, there \Nis zero chance of them dodging!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.66,0:19:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In exchange, they require \Npin-point accuracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.39,0:19:12.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And there is a crazy huge distance \Nbetween me and my target!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.92,0:19:16.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ve gotta account for the earth’s \Nrotation, vibrations in the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.21,0:19:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and even gravitational interference!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.60,0:19:20.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, at least I don’t have to \Nworry about the Coriolis Effect
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.42,0:19:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,like I do when sniping on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.31,0:19:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To top it off, I’ve \Ngotta fire at max power.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.40,0:19:28.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So once I let her rip, it’ll take \Na while before I can fire again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.86,0:19:30.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even on Earth, I’m \Nprobably the only person
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.84,0:19:32.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,capable of pulling this mission off!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.91,0:19:39.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We’ll help adjust the laser’s sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.75,0:19:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But since the enemy is moving,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.92,0:19:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,everything ultimately rests \Non the skill of the gunner.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.17,0:19:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.09,0:19:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, I know! You can count on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.26,0:19:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want something if I pull this off.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.97,0:19:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like one of the GDF’s \NG-11, Steyr-ACE or IWS-2000!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.25,0:19:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right. I’ll take \Nit into consideration.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.76,0:19:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fer real?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.39,0:20:01.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may pull the trigger \Nwhen you’re ready,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.51,0:20:03.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but don’t take too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.64,0:20:05.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.69,0:20:08.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You’re really pilin’ on the \Npressure by actin’ all nice...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.65,0:20:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold 4 is ready to snipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.85,0:20:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do something to restrict \Nthe enemy’s movements.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.94,0:20:15.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case--!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.49,0:20:45.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you’ve done it, \Nprimitive creature!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.73,0:20:48.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you make me lick \Nyour planet’s dirt!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.68,0:20:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, while the enemy is still dazed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.66,0:20:54.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t push me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.70,0:20:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I’m not careful, Izuru \Nmight get caught in the blast!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.06,0:23:56.08,Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,“Defensive Battle at\NCosmopolitan Academy (Second Part)”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.08,0:23:58.08,Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,
